  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I be manlier as a 15yo?",
  "response": "Becoming \"manlier\" is about developing confidence, self-respect, and maturity rather than conforming to stereotypes. Here are some practical and healthy ways to grow into your best self at 15:\n\n### 1. **Build Confidence**\n   - **Set Goals**: Focus on personal growth, whether it\u2019s in academics, sports, or hobbies.\n   - **Step Out of Your Comfort Zone**: Try new activities, speak up in class, or take on challenges.\n   - **Take Pride in Your Appearance**: Dress well, maintain good hygiene, and stand tall with good posture.\n\n### 2. **Develop Emotional Intelligence**\n   - **Be Kind and Respectful**: Treat others with compassion, regardless of gender or background.\n   - **Express Your Emotions**: It\u2019s okay to feel sad, angry, or vulnerable. Being in touch with your emotions is a sign of strength, not weakness.\n   - **Listen Actively**: Show empathy by genuinely listening to others.\n\n### 3. **Take Responsibility**\n   - **Own Your Actions**: Admit mistakes and learn from them.\n   - **Help Out at Home**: Contribute by doing chores, helping with siblings, or assisting your family.\n   - **Be Reliable**: Keep your word and follow through on commitments.\n\n### 4. **Improve Physical and Mental Health**\n   - **Exercise Regularly**: Stay active through sports, gym workouts, or outdoor activities.\n   - **Eat Healthily**: Fuel your body with nutritious foods.\n   - **Practice Self-Care**: Get enough sleep, manage stress, and take care of your mental health.\n\n### 5. **Learn Practical Skills**\n   - **DIY Basics**: Learn how to fix things, use tools, or handle minor repairs.\n   - **Financial Literacy**: Start saving money, budgeting, and understanding how to manage finances.\n   - **Cooking**: Knowing how to prepare meals is a valuable life skill.\n\n### 6. **Be a Good Friend and Role Model**\n   - **Support Others**: Be there for your friends and family when they need you.\n   - **Stand Up for What\u2019s Right**: Don\u2019t be afraid to speak out against bullying or injustice.\n   - **Be Humble**: Celebrate your achievements without bragging.\n\n### 7. **Cultivate Interests and Passions**\n   - **Explore Hobbies**: Find something you\u2019re passionate about, whether it\u2019s music, art, coding, or sports.\n   - **Stay Curious**: Read, learn, and ask questions to broaden your knowledge.\n\n### 8. **Respect Yourself and Others**\n   - **Set Boundaries**: Don\u2019t let others pressure you into doing something you\u2019re uncomfortable with.\n   - **Respect Differences**: Embrace diversity and treat everyone with dignity.\n\n### 9. **Focus on Personal Growth Over Appearance**\n   - Strength and masculinity aren\u2019t about muscles or looks but about character, integrity, and how you treat others.\n\n### 10. **Be Patient with Yourself**\n   - Growing into who you want to be takes time. Focus on progress, not perfection.\n\nRemember, being \"manly\" is about being a good person, not fitting into a rigid stereotype. Embrace your individuality and work on becoming the best version of yourself!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
